text: The legend of Arthur pulling the sword from the stone comes from the poor metallurgy knowledge of native Britons at the time. A warlord who knew how to make steel from iron ore (ie "pulling" a sword from stone) would have been able to use this superior military technology to dominate the tribes and unite Britain. Thus the legend spread. Those wishing to visit Arthur's country should go to Tintagel castle, Cornwall, England. In a nearby wood lies a fallen menhir engraved in 1600 year old Druid runes "Here lies Latinus son of Arthur the Great".
